Ways to store/read data
    localStorage vs cookies vs sessionStorage:
     Permanence of data:
     - localStorage keeps the info across browser sessions/pages
     - sessionStorage keeps the info across browser session/pages
     - cookies doesn't keep the info across browser session/pages
     Place to save:
     - localStorage saves on the local user computer
     - sessionStorage saves on the local user computer
     - cookies doesn't save on the local user computer(is embedded)
     Usage of data:
     - localStorage is used only for client-side reads, we can't not access from server
     - sessionStorage is used only for server-side reads, we can't not access from client-side 
     - cookies can be used for read server-side and also client side
     Secure:
     - The most secure are cookies only https or localStorage for our jwt or credentials!
    
